description: This file is a generated Java class used by Flutter to register Android plugins with the Flutter engine. It programmatically adds plugin instances for shared preferences and SQLite database functionality into the Flutter engine during app initialization.

classes.name: GeneratedPluginRegistrant
classes.description: A utility class automatically generated to register Flutter plugins with the Android engine. Contains static method for plugin registration.

methods.name: registerWith
methods.description: Registers plugins with the provided FlutterEngine instance by adding plugin instances to its plugin registry. Handles exceptions during registration to prevent crashes.
